         "content_html" : "\n<p>Kif Leswing, reporting for CNBC:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Facebook parent Meta said on Wednesday that the privacy change\nApple made to its iOS operating system last year will decrease the\nsocial media companyâ€™s sales this year by about $10 billion. â€œWe\nbelieve the impact of iOS overall is a headwind on our business in\n2022,â€ Meta CFO Dave Wehner said on a call with analysts after the\ncompanyâ€™s fourth-quarter earnings report. â€œItâ€™s on the order of\n$10 billion, so itâ€™s a pretty significant headwind for our\nbusiness.â€</p>\n\n<p>Facebookâ€™s admission is the most concrete data point so far on the\nimpact to the advertising industry of Appleâ€™s App Tracking\nTransparency feature, which reduces targeting capabilities by\nlimiting advertisers from accessing an iPhone user identifier.</p>\n\n<p>Meta shares sank 23% in extended trading on Wednesday after the\ncompany warned about numerous challenges and came up short on user\nnumbers. Facebook said first quarter revenue will be $27 billion\nto $29 billion, while analysts were expecting that number to\nexceed $30 billion.</p>\n\n<p>Wehner said the $10 billion revenue hit this year is merely a\nbest guess.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>Facebookâ€™s stock stayed down all day, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/2/3/22916007/facebook-meta-stock-drop-history-invest\">wiping $200 billion in value from the companyâ€™s market cap</a>â€‰â€”â€‰the biggest one-day drop in market value ever. Couldnâ€™t happen to a nicer company.</p>\n\n<p>Worth noting that <a href=\"https://s21.q4cdn.com/399680738/files/doc_financials/2021/q4/Meta-Q4-2021-Earnings-Call-Transcript.pdf\">on Facebookâ€™s analyst call</a>, when pressed on this $10 billion figure, Wehner offered nothing to back it up. Really strong vibes of â€œ<em>The problem isnâ€™t us, or our productsâ€‰â€”â€‰itâ€™s mean old anti-competitive Apple.</em>â€ It doesnâ€™t seem like anyone bought that line.</p>\n\n<p class=\"x-netnewswire-hide\" style=\"padding-top: 1.5em;\"><em>Link: <strong><a href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2022/02/02/facebook-says-apple-ios-privacy-change-will-cost-10-billion-this-year.html\">cnbc.com/2022/02/02/facebook-says-apple-ios-privacy-changeâ€¦</a></strong></em></p>\n"
